v8:item.v8:content: Select catalog to import data to
Select catalog to import data to
Select a catalog to import spreadsheet data to. You can paste the data from the clipboard or upload a spreadsheet file.
Copy data from a spreadsheet file and paste it to the table.

Save the template to a file, open it in a spreadsheet editor and enter the data. Then import the spreadsheet to the application. The application supports the following formats: • Microsoft Excel 97 Workbook (.xls) or Microsoft Excel 2007 Workbook (.xlsx) • LibreOffice Calc Spreadsheet (.ods) • Comma-separated values file (.csv) • Spreadsheet document (.mxl)
Cannot add the items to the list because no matches have been found.
%2 out of %1 lines will be added into the list.
Some of the rows will be skipped: • No matches found: 8 • Multiple matches found: 2 To review and resolve the skipped rows, click "Next".
Cannot map some items because they have no matches or multiple matches. To add an item manually, select the correct object in the "Object" column.
Some imported items have no matches. You can add them as new items or skip them. To map them manually, enter the data in column "%1".

Some imported items have multiple matches. They are highlighted in <colorstyle -16>red</>.
You can map them manually or add them as new items.
Select catalog columns that you want to map to the spreadsheet columns.

Map imported data to catalog items. You can map data to each column. To map a single row, select a column value.
Unmapped data can be skipped or added as new items. Mapped data can be updated or skipped.

You can edit items imported to the "%1" catalog. To do so, select the items and select "Edit attributes". To edit a single item, double-click it. Also, you can save skipped lines to a file, revise them, and import them later.
Open the "%1" catalog after you finish import
Save the template as a spreadsheet file. The following formats are supported: Microsoft Excel 2007 Workbook, Comma-separated values file (CSV), or MXL spreadsheet.
Select "Edit template" to edit the column titles and order. You can save the template and use it for future data import.
